Pre-Game Insights: Germany midfielder Aleksandar Pavlovic will be back from injury for their Nations League match at home to Netherlands on Monday and will form a midfield partnership with Angelo Stiller.
Germany coach Julian Nagelsmann praised Pavlovic and Stiller as prospects for the team ahead of the 2026 World Cup.
Germany, who drew 2-2 with the Dutch in Amsterdam in September, are top of Nations League Group A3 on seven points from three matches, with Netherlands second on five.
Nagelsmann mentioned that the game against Netherlands will be interesting and that Germany will be more pushed than they were against Bosnia.
